    • Method Detail

      • copyTo

        public ImageCore copyTo(ImageCore destinationImage)
        Description copied from interface: ImageDomainTransform
        Copies this image into another image, which must have been previously allocated. The size of the destination image must agree in all dimensions with the size the original image, and the two images must have same bitdepth. The destination image's calibration and other metadata is merged with that of the original image (and replace for parameters that already exist in the destination image's metadata). The implementation might require that both source and destination images should be defined on the same Image Processing Framework (i.e. Created by the same ImageCore factory).
        Specified by:
        copyTo in interface ImageDomainTransform
        Specified by:
        copyTo in class ImageDomainTransformGeneric
        Parameters:
        destinationImage - The destination image into which the voxels gray levels should be copies, swapping two coordinates in the voxels' domain.
        Returns:
        The reference to destinationImage for use in the cascade pattern
